narrative.title: Provider Overview
narrative.text: Southeast Alaska Regional Health Consortium is a Community/Behavioral Health provider based in Juneau, AK. From the 2018–2024 period, this provider received $19.9M in Medicaid payments across 32K claims serving 0 beneficiaries.

narrative.title: Why This Matters
narrative.text: At $19.9M in Medicaid payments, this provider represents significant public healthcare spending. Understanding where these dollars go helps ensure the program serves those who need it most.
